Here is a simple approach to solve this question.
What we are doing here is
i) if(n&1) is equal to 1 then find next 1
		........**(subcondition)**.........if(n==0) then it means next 1 not found else 1 is found so set the value of max
ii) else right shift.

```class Solution {
    public int binaryGap(int n) {
        int max=0;
        while(n>0){
            int r=n&1;
			//if r==1 then search next occurence of 1
            if(r==1){
                n=n>>1;
                int var=1;
                while(n>0 && (n&1)!=1){
                    n=n>>1;
                    var++;
                }
                if(n!=0){
                    max=Math.max(max,var);
                }
                // else right shift
            }else{
                n=n>>1;
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}```

