Every odd value will have a 1 on the right hand side of the binary digit (because this is the ones digit and all factors of 2 are even except 2 raised to the 0 power).  We can then bitwise right shift by 1 (i.e. integer division by 2, effectively dropping the right digit) to 'traverse' across the binary and count the times until we obtain another odd (1) value.

```
class Solution:
    def binaryGap(self, n: int) -> int:

        ans = 0
        while n > 1:
            if n % 2 == 1:
                count = 1
                n >>= 1
                while n % 2 == 0:
                    count += 1
                    n >>= 1
                ans = max(ans, count)
            else:
                n >>= 1

        return ans
```

