solutions.content:
Just maintain a variable which is a power of 2 (i.e. contains only 1 one). We right shift this every time in a loop taking at max 32 right shfift for an integer. Simply keep track of `lastPosition` where we found a one and a `max` distance between 1's. 
```
class  Solution {
    public int binaryGap(int N) {
        int dist = 1, lastPos = -1, incr = 0 ; 
        int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE; 
        while(dist <= N){
            dist = 1 << incr; 
            if((dist & N) > 0 ){
                if(lastPos != -1)max = Math.max(max, incr - lastPos); 
                lastPos = incr; 
            }
            incr++; 
        }
        return max==Integer.MIN_VALUE ? 0 : max; 
    }
}
```

