**Explanation**
1) Store the count of digits of given n in an array.
2) Store the count of digits of every power of 2 from 1 to 30.
3) If the count of digits in any of the power of 2 matches with the count of digits of given n, then return true. 
4) If a match is not found after all iterations, that means the given number cannot be arranged in the form of a power of 2. Hence, return false.
```
class Solution 
{
    public boolean reorderedPowerOf2(int n) 
    {
        int[] cnt = new int[10];
        int num = n;
        while(num != 0)
        {
            cnt[num % 10]++;
            num /= 10;
        }

        int two = 1;
        int pow = 1;
        while(pow <= 30)
        {
            int cur[] = new int[10];
            num = two;
            while(num != 0)
            {
                cur[num % 10]++;
                num /= 10;
            }

            boolean powOfTwo = true;
            for(int i=0; i<10; i++)
            {
                if(cnt[i] != cur[i])
                {
                    powOfTwo = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(powOfTwo)
                return true;
            two *= 2;
            pow++;
        }
        return false;
    }   
}
```

