solutions.content:
# Approach
Explanation.

**Occur** is an 2d array which stores occurrences of all digits of each number (power of 2). 

Example: 2^16 = 65536, array with occurences of digits for it will be: [0,0,0,1,0,2,2,0,0,0], because we have one occurence of 3, two occurences of 5, and two occurences of 6.

**Occur** is $$static$$ because I fill it only once and use for each test case.

The names of methods are self explainable.

# Code
```
class Solution {

    static byte[][] ocurr;

    public boolean reorderedPowerOf2(int n) {
        if (n == 1) return true;
        if (ocurr == null) {
            ocurr = fillOccurencesForEachPowerOf2();
        }

        byte[] freq = countFreqs(n);
        for (byte[] oc : ocurr) {
            if (areSame(oc, freq)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    private byte[][] fillOccurencesForEachPowerOf2() {
        byte[][] res = new byte[30][10];
        for (int i = 0; i < res.length; i++) {
            int pow = (int) Math.pow(2, i);
            res[i] = countFreqs(pow);
        }
        return res;
    }

    private byte[] countFreqs(int pow) {
        byte[] freq = new byte[10];
        while (pow > 0) {
            int digit = pow % 10;
            //increment digits frequency for number pow
            freq[digit]++;
            pow /= 10;
        }
        return freq;
    }

    private boolean areSame(byte[] oc, byte[] freq) {
        for (int i = 0; i < oc.length; i++) {
            if (oc[i] != freq[i]) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```

