From the problem description it is clear that we need to check whether N is a permutation of a power of 2. The approach is the following:

In the first step, we count the occurance of each digit (0-9) in N

In the second step, we go through each power of 2 (say, x). For each x, we do the following:
1. Count the occurance of each digit in x
2. We compare the occurance of digits in x with that of N. If we find a match, we return true.
3. If we don't find a match for any x, we return false.

For example, for N = 83461, the counts will match for x = 16384 and thus we will return true. For, N = 10000, the counts will not match for any x, so we will return false.

```
	public boolean reorderedPowerOf2(int N) {
        int[] dcountN = getDigitCount(N);

        for(int i = 0; i < 31; i++){
            int x = 1 << i, j;
            int[] dcountX = getDigitCount(x);

            for(j = 0; j < 10 && dcountN[j] == dcountX[j]; j++);
			/*if j becomes 10 after above loop, it means the counts
			  of the digits are the same in x and N*/
            if(j == 10) return true;
        }

        return false;
    }

    private int[] getDigitCount(int x){
        int[] result = new int[10];
        while(x > 0){
            result[x % 10]++;
            x /= 10;
        }
        return result;
    }

