# Approach
Put Digits of n in a vector(Suppose G) and then find a power of 2 that has digits as vector G if we find that both have same digits return true else false.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: 0ms,better than 100% online CPP Solutions

- Space complexity: 6.36mb better than 40.61% online CPP Solutions

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool reorderedPowerOf2(int n) {
        vector<int> g;
        while(n)
        {
            g.push_back(n%10);
            n/=10;
        }
        sort(g.begin(),g.end());
        for(int i=0;;i++)
        {
            vector<int> v;
            long long int t=pow(2,i);
            while(t)
            {
               v.push_back(t%10);
               t/=10;
            }
            sort(v.begin(),v.end());
            if(v==g)
            return true;

            if(v.size()>g.size())
            break;
        }
        return false;
    }
};
```

