# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- There are 31 powers of 2 that are within the question constraints of `1 <= n <= 10^9`
- Sort the number `n` and each sorted power of 2 from 0 -> 30
- Leading 0 case is handled because the ordered power will never have a 0. For example, 0256 and 256 are not.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(nlogn*n)$$ Sort * string creation
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean reorderedPowerOf2(int n) {
        char[] numArray = String.valueOf(n).toCharArray();
        Arrays.sort(numArray);
        String orderedNum = new String(numArray);

        for (int i = 0; i < 31; i++) {
            int powerNum = (int) Math.pow(2, i);
            char[] powerNumArray = String.valueOf(powerNum).toCharArray();
            Arrays.sort(powerNumArray);
            String orderedPower = new String(powerNumArray);

            if (orderedNum.equals(orderedPower)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
